<doc id="840606" wikidata="Q7901635" url="?curid=840606" title="Us (Mull Historical Society album)">
<text>Us is the second album from Scottish indie band Mull Historical Society, and the follow-up to &quot;Loss&quot;. It includes the singles &quot;The Final Arrears&quot; and &quot;Am I Wrong&quot;. &quot;Us&quot; (2003) received generally positive reviews; &quot;NME&quot; called it &quot;a joyous slice of orchestral prozac&quot;. The track &quot;The Supermarket Strikes Back&quot; is a riposte to &quot;Barcode Bypass&quot; from &quot;Loss&quot;. After the album was released the record label, Warners, dropped the band.

